# Analysis of DNA Sequence & Protein using Biopython
In the file ```Oikopleura_transcripts_reference_v1.0.fa.txt``` taken from ```http://oikoarrays.biology.uiowa.edu/Oiko/Downloads.html```, DNA sequences of the organism "Oikopleura dioica" are given.
I have created a program called analysis.py which will read the sequences from the above FASTA file, print the general information about the each DNA such as ID, and length of the DNA, and then I am using the packages and modules from [BioPython](https://biopython.org/) to do simple analysis on the sequence.

I am using various functions to :
- get the GC content of the DNA Sequence.
- get the complement and reverse complement of the DNA Sequence.
- get the RNA sequence by transcribing the DNA Sequence.
- Get the Protein Sequence if the DNA sequence is unambiguous. After getting the protein sequence, a protein analysis is done to get the following :
    - Molecular Weight of the protein
    - Aromaticity of protein
    - Instability Index of Protein
    - Isoelectric Point of Protein
    - Count & Percentage of Amino Acids in the Protein

## How to run the program
Execute the program by running 
```
python3 Analysis.py
```
Ensure the file ```Oikopleura_transcripts_reference_v1.0.fa.txt``` is in the same folder as the python file.
After running the program, you will get prompted to choose whether you want the analysis of a single DNA sequence or all DNA sequences given in the file.
